I'm a big admirer
of yours, Mr. Earp.

40:25.625 --> 40:28.709
Narrator:
<i> Earp even inspires</i>
<i> a young production assistant</i>

40:28.709 --> 40:31.417
<i> named Marion Morrison,</i>

40:31.417 --> 40:33.542
<i> who will go on</i>
<i> to become an actor,</i>

40:33.583 --> 40:37.500
<i> taking the stage name</i>
<i> John Wayne.</i>

40:37.500 --> 40:39.583
<i> John Wayne</i>
<i> uses Wyatt Earp</i>

40:39.583 --> 40:42.667
<i> as the model for many</i>
<i> of his Hollywood roles,</i>

40:42.667 --> 40:45.917
<i> creating an iconic image</i>
<i> of the Western hero</i>

40:45.917 --> 40:48.875
<i> and becoming one of the most</i>
<i> prominent western stars</i>

40:48.875 --> 40:50.542
<i> in movie history.</i>

40:52.000 --> 40:53.750
Danny Glover:
<i> The attachment to westerns</i>

40:53.750 --> 40:56.458
<i> were certainly,</i>
<i> I think, an important part</i>

40:56.458 --> 40:59.001
of this country's evolution,

40:59.001 --> 41:01.583
it's sense of it's identity,

41:01.583 --> 41:03.125
<i> it's sense of freedom.</i>

41:05.500 --> 41:07.500
Narrator:
<i> To this day,</i>
<i> the West is remembered</i>

41:07.500 --> 41:10.792
<i> as an era of violence</i>
<i> and lawlessness</i>

41:10.792 --> 41:12.959
<i> defined by</i>
<i> larger-than-life figures</i>

41:12.959 --> 41:15.667
<i> like Jesse James,</i>
<i> Crazy Horse,</i>

41:15.667 --> 41:18.542
<i> Custer,</i>
<i> Billy the Kid,</i>

41:18.542 --> 41:21.667
<i> Sitting Bull,</i>
<i> and Wyatt Earp.</i>

41:21.667 --> 41:23.625
<i> ( woman screams )</i>

41:23.667 --> 41:25.834
Narrator:
<i> They were men who took</i>
<i> what they wanted</i>

41:25.834 --> 41:28.792
<i> and fought for</i>
<i> what they believed in.</i>

41:28.792 --> 41:31.750
Brands:
<i> The outlaws were in some ways</i>
<i> the ultimate individualists.</i>

41:31.750 --> 41:33.834
<i> No one could tell</i>
<i> the outlaws what to do.</i>

41:33.834 --> 41:35.583
A lot of Americans
could imagine,

41:35.583 --> 41:37.500
"Boy, if things
had been different,

41:37.500 --> 41:39.542
I could be as bold
and brave

41:39.583 --> 41:43.583
as daring as Jesse James
or as Billy the Kid.

41:43.583 --> 41:46.667
Tom Skerrit:
<i> The Old West engaged</i>
<i> your imagination</i>

41:46.667 --> 41:48.750
in a way nothing else
has ever done.

41:48.792 --> 41:52.959
And it really is
that eternal American figure,

41:52.959 --> 41:57.667
<i> that guy who faces adversity</i>
<i> and comes through it.</i>

41:59.583 --> 42:01.542
Narrator:
<i> The story of the West</i>
<i> is the story</i>

42:01.542 --> 42:03.917
<i> of a country</i>
<i> evolving and growing</i>

42:03.917 --> 42:07.834
<i> through the sheer will</i>
<i> and courage of its people.</i>

42:07.834 --> 42:11.083
I believe that
it is truly American

42:11.083 --> 42:14.583
<i> to strike out in a new life,</i>
<i> in a new existence.</i>

42:14.583 --> 42:18.959
<i> The hardships on those</i>
<i> individuals is amazing.</i>

42:18.959 --> 42:21.083
<i> And despite</i>
<i> all the obstacles,</i>

42:21.125 --> 42:25.041
we've populated a nation
that is now and always has been

42:25.041 --> 42:27.709
one of the great
experiments in history.
